cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language inference (NLI), which is a subfield of computational linguistics and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses machine learning models and their performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning models such as BERT, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of syntactic heuristics, which could also relate to computer vision and image processing (cs.CV).
